Novartis Will Boost R&D Spending, Cut Costs, Jimenez Tells Euro

-- B y   C h r i s t i a n   V i t s
-- 
2011-10-02T10:49:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-02/novartis-will-boost-r-d-spending-cut-costs-jimenez-tells-euro.html
Novartis AG (NOVN)  Chief Executive Officer
Joseph Jimenez said the company will “most likely” increase
its research and development investments in each of the coming
five years,  Euro am Sonntag  reported, citing an interview.  Jimenez aims to cut marketing costs and boost capacity
utilization, according to the report. Novartis expects to profit
from its suppliers’ austerity programs, he was cited as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Christian Vits in Frankfurt at 
 cvits@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Craig Stirling at   cstirling1@bloomberg.net  